This privacy policy (“Policy”) describes how
Real News Now
collects, uses, and shares the personal data of users of Real News Now Products (“Apps”).  Real News Now is committed to protecting the privacy rights of its users and providing transparent information about the data collection and usage practices of the Apps.
Scope of this Policy:
This Policy applies to personal data processed by  Real News Now in connection with the Apps.
Data Collection and Use:
Real News Now collects the following data from users of the Apps:
User account information, such as username and password
In-app activity, such as scores and achievements
Device information, such as device type and operating system
Location data, such as IP address
This data is used to provide and improve the Apps, as well as to analyze and understand the behavior of users.  Real News Now may also use this data for marketing purposes, such as sending promotional offers and advertisements to users.
Data Sharing:
Real News Now may share users’ personal data with third-party service providers for the purpose of providing and improving the Apps. These third-party service providers are contractually obligated to maintain the confidentiality and security of the personal data they process on behalf of  Real News Now.
In addition,  Real News Now may also share aggregated, de-identified, or anonymous data with marketers, advertisers, and other third parties for marketing and advertising purposes. This data will not contain any personally identifiable information.
Data Retention:
Real News Now will retain users’ personal data for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes described in this Policy, or as required by applicable law.
Rights of Data Subjects:
Under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), users have the following rights in relation to their personal data:
Right of access:
users have the right to access their personal data and obtain information about how their data is processed.
Right to rectification:
Users have the right to request the correction of inaccurate personal data.
Right to erasure:
users have the right to request the deletion of their personal data.
Right to restrict processing: users have the right to request the restriction of the processing of their personal data.
Right to object:
Users have the right to object to the processing of their personal data for certain purposes, such as direct marketing.
Right to data portability:
users have the right to receive their personal data in a structured, commonly used, and machine-readable format, and to transmit their data to another controller.
To exercise these rights, users can contact Merica Now at
Realnewsnowcontact@gmail.com
.
Merica Now will respond to all requests within a reasonable timeframe and provide any requested information free of charge, unless the request is manifestly unfounded or excessive.
Changes to this Policy:
Real News Now may modify this Policy from time to time. If significant changes are made,  Real News Now will provide notice to users through the Apps or by other means.
Contact Information:
If you have any questions or concerns about this Policy or  Real News Now’s privacy practices, please contact us at
Realnewsnowcontact@gmail.com
.